I feel your pain.
We have the exact same issue with running the exact same pathplanner test in our Auto.
The auto drives straight for a bit, then rotates around by 180 degrees.
Teleop driving works just fine.
Going to try these steps from the YAGSL V1 thread to see if we have some module defined incorrectly/backwards:
Start by uninverting your IMU and drive motors
THEN inverting your IMU
THEN invert your drive motors
THEN uninvert your IMU

THEN flip modules
THEN uninvert your drive motors
THEN invert your IMU
THEN invert your drive motors

Then you must be testing wrong, have bad hardware, or something of that nature if you get to this step.
